Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}. Peel and grate the @garlic{3%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @panko breadcrumbs{10}, @Italian style herbs{1}, @salt{} and @water{2} for the breadcrumbs and one third of the garlic.

Add the @British beef mince{240} to the breadcrumbs. Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands.

Roll into even-sized balls, 5 per person, and pop them onto a large #baking tray{}.

Bake the meatballs on the top shelf of your oven until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, remove from the oven.

Meanwhile, add the @spaghetti{180} to the pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{8%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and stir to stop it sticking together.

While the spaghetti cooks, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{for frying} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the pan is hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook lardons thoroughly.

Add half the remaining garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%secs}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1/2}, @red wine jus paste{22}, @sugar{1} and @water{200} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{5-6%mins}.

Meanwhile, halve the @ciabatta{1} and lay onto a baking tray, cut-side up. Spread over the remaining garlic and drizzle with the @olive oil{1} for the garlic bread.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{6-7%mins}.

When everything's ready, add the meatballs and cooked spaghetti to the sauce. Toss to coat, then simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}. Add splash of water if it's a little dry.

Drizzle the @Parmigiano Reggiano{40}(grated) through your ultimate spaghetti and meatballs, then remove from the heat and share between your bowls.

Drizzle the @wild rocket{20} with the @balsamic glaze{12} and serve alongside.

Pop the garlic bread on the side to finish.

Enjoy!